#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.17:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Anusayavagga"
msgstr "2. Tendencies"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Dukkhānupassīsutta"
msgstr "17. Observing Suffering"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.17:1.1"
msgid ""
"Sattime, bhikkhave, puggalā āhuneyyā … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these seven people are worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy of "
"greeting with joined palms, and are the supreme field of merit for the world."

msgctxt "an7.17:1.2"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "an7.17:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sabbasaṅkhāresu dukkhānupassī viharati … pe "
"…."
msgstr ""
"First, take a person who meditates observing suffering in all conditions. "
"They perceive suffering and experience suffering. Constantly, continually, "
"and without stopping, they apply the mind and fathom with wisdom. …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.17:1.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
